<body>The sum of the squares of the first ten natural numbers is 12 + 22 + ... + 102 = 385<br><br>
The square of the sum of the first ten natural numbers is, (1 + 2 + ... + 10)^2 = 552^2 = 3025<br><br>
Hence the difference between the sum of the squares of the first ten natural numbers and the square of the sum is 3025 - 385 = 2640.<br><br>
Find the difference between the sum of the squares of the first one hundred natural numbers (x = 100) and the square of the sum. <br><br>

<input type="text" id="input" placeholder = "x">
<button onclick="showAnswerDiv()">Activate Script</button> <br><br>
<div id="answerDiv" style="display:none">Answer Div</div>

<script>
var answerDiv = document.getElementById('answerDiv');

function sumOfSquares(lastInSeries) {
    sum = 0;
    for (i=1;i<=lastInSeries;i++) {
        sum+=i*i;
    }
    return sum;
}

function squareOfSums (lastInSeries) {
    sum = 0;
    for (i=1;i<=lastInSeries;i++) {
    sum +=i;
    }
    return sum * sum;
}

function produceAnswer(lastInSeries) {
return squareOfSums(lastInSeries) - sumOfSquares(lastInSeries);
}


function showAnswerDiv() {
    answerDiv.innerHTML = produceAnswer(document.getElementById('input').value);
    answerDiv.style.display = 'block';
    }

</script>

</body>
</html> 
